properties.Name: LogMeanTemperatureDifference
properties.Description:
The heat exchanger log mean temperature difference recorded for the associated period.

The driving temperature across the heat transfer surface varies with position, but an appropriate mean temperature can be defined. In most simple systems this is the "log mean temperature difference" (LMTD). Sometimes direct knowledge of the LMTD is not available and the NTU method is used.

Columns.Name: HeatExchangerId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Component.

Columns.Name: InputStreamTemperatureC
Columns.Description: The input stream temperature of the heat exchanger in C.

Columns.Name: OutputStreamTemperatureC
Columns.Description: The output stream temperature of the heat exchanger in C.

Columns.Name: LogMeanTemperatureDifferenceC
Columns.Description: The log mean temperature different between the input and output stream of the heat exchanger for the associated period.

Columns.Name: LogMeanTemperatureDifferenceNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the log mean temperature difference.
